      "span_text": "The experiments were carried out on 46 eyecup preparations of frog (Rana ridibunda), continuously superfused with Ringer solution (NaCl 110 mM, KCl 2.6 mM, NaHCO 3 10 mM, CaCl 2 1.6 mM, MgCl 2 0.8 mM, Glucose 2 mM; HCl 0.5 mM to adjust pH to 7.8) at a rate of 1.8-2.0 ml/min, temperature 16-18°C and supplied with moistened O 2 (for details see"
